
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-koodli-netext-multiaccess-indicator-03.txt'>
    <title>"Multi-access Indicator for Mobility", Rajeev Koodli, Jouni Korhonen</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-koodli-netext-multiaccess-indicator-03.txt</link>
    <description>When a Mobile Node attaches to the mobile network using multiple access networks, it is important for the Mobile Network Gateway to know whether the Mobile Node is capable of simultaneous multi-access, so that the former can distribute the traffic flows using the most appropriate interface.  This document defines a new EAP attribute which can be used for such an indication to the Mobile Network Gateway.  The document also reserves a new MIP6-Feature-Vector flag.</description>
    <dc:date>2012-03-01T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
